KPI Sheet 2 (Total Orders) 12


1. Right click on Total Sales worksheet and select Duplicate. Rename the new sheet as Total Orders.


2. Remove all the values from Marks card. Drag and drop Orders Per day, Quantity, Orders MoM, Total Orders KPI Indicator Down, Total Orders KPI Indicator UP to Text under Marks card.

3. Click on Text and then click Ellipses. Select <AGG(Orders Per Day)> , Font = Tableau Medium, Size = 10, Bold, Alignment = Center, Color = #ff7400.

4. Select <SUM(Quanity)>. Font = Tableau Bold, Size = 16, Alignment = Center, Color = #000000

5.Arrange <AGG(Orders MoM %)> <AGG(Total Orders KPI Indicator Down)> <AGG(Total Orders KPI Indicator UP)> in the same line. 

Select <AGG(Orders MoM %)> <AGG(Total Orders KPI Indicator Down)> <AGG(Total Orders KPI Indicator UP)>. Font = Tableau Medium, Bold, Alignment Center. 

<AGG(Orders MoM %)> Size = 10, Color = #747474,

<AGG(Total Orders KPI Indicator Down)> Size=12, Color = #aa0000,

<AGG(Total Orders KPI Indicator Up)> Size=12, Color = #005500

Click OK.

6. Click on Text and Alignment. Select Center alignment for both Horizontal and Verticle.

7. Click on Tooltip under Marks and enter the following text:

Total Orders: <SUM(Quantity)>

 Orders MoM: <AGG(Orders MoM %)>

 Orders Per day: <AGG(Orders Per day)>

Font = Tableau Book, Size = 10, Alignment = Left

Total Orders, Orders MoM, Orderss Per Day – Color = #787878

<SUM(Quantity)>, <AGG(Orders MoM%)>, <AGG(Orders Per Day)> - Color = #333333

8. Drag and drop Date Filter to Filters shelf and select only True option.

9. Click on Title, Edit Title. Enter the text Total Orders.
